OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FRadio mostly ignores female
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdance acts, study says     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Less than one per cent of the dance    
OL,6, music played on UK radio is made by a  
OL,7, female solo artist or all-female band, 
OL,8, a new study suggests.                  
OL,10,FWomen are also under-represented on the
OL,11,Fcharts, accounting for just 5% of dance
OL,12,Fhits, according to the report, which   
OL,13,Fexamines gender imbalance in the scene.
OL,15,FTo get heard, it says, female acts have
OL,16,Fto collaborate with male producers.    
OL,18,FSongs with women as the "featured"     
OL,19,Fvocalist make up 44% of dance music on 
OL,20,Fthe radio and 37% of chart hits.       
